    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I wish to speak about the state of Major League Baseball. I love the game. I follow my favorite team, the Kansas City Royals, through winning and losing seasons. But I will not watch a single minute of this year's World Series because the New York Yankees are playing.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I wish to speak about the state of Major League Baseball. I love the game. I follow my favorite team, the Kansas City Royals, through winning and losing seasons. But I will not watch a single minute of this year's World Series because the New York Yankees are playing.</p>
        <p>I will not subject myself to the sight of George Steinbrenner crying with happiness because he bought another championship.</p>
        <p>Two teams from that city will play in the Series. This is fitting as baseball has become the survival of the financially fittest.</p>
        <p>DANIEL P. SCHAMLE  Lawrence, Kan.</p>
      </block>
